# JGI Import Results

This Narrative contains your data import, which you will find listed as the sole item in the DATA panel

In order to locate apps which can utilize this data you can use the data item itself to filter the apps available through the APPS Panel.

To do this:

- Hover your mouse over the data item, and then click on *options button* (<img style="display:inline; margin: 0" src="data:image/jpeg;base64,">) button which appears on the right hand side.
- A set of buttons appear below.
- Click on the left-most button, the *input filter* &nbsp;  (<img style="display: inline; margin: 0" src="data:image/jpeg;base64,">)
- this will cause the APPS panel to display only those apps which take objects of this type as input.
    
After finding an app you would like to use, click on the app icon or title to insert it into the Narrative.
